Research for essay
==================

Jan Tschichold
---------------
Was a typographer, book designer, teacher and writer. Between 1926 and 1929, he designed a “universal alphabet” to clean up the few multigraphs and non-phonetic spellings in the German language.



![tschichold_portrait_d12383i43](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8985471/5062078/88f484fa-6daa-11e4-9629-b713871e988a.jpg)

Jan Tschichold claimed that he was one of the most powerful influences on 20th century typography. The son of a sign painter and trained in calligraphy, Tschichold began working with typography at a very early age

Sabon was one of Tschichold's completed typefaces as seen below:
![sabon](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8985471/5061945/cd9954b4-6da5-11e4-8002-17e72caf9d45.jpg)

He was also very much known for his career with Penguin Books and while he was there he developed a standardized practice for creating the covers for all of the books produced by Penguin.

![penguin-2](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8985471/5061957/47c58e38-6da6-11e4-9a0b-272a012752f7.jpg)

-----------------------------------------------
