Paul Rand
----------
Was an American art director and graphic designer, best known for his corporate logo designs and helped establish the so-called Swiss Style of design in the United States.

![paul-rand](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8985471/5062075/82cc63cc-6daa-11e4-8bb5-59befaa8e6f9.jpg)

His work:
=========

![rand4_0](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8985471/5062082/d08580c6-6daa-11e4-9ba6-5296a2cecb8c.jpg)
![dsc_2591](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8985471/5062086/e8a33702-6daa-11e4-95f1-265655a4370e.jpg)

His logo Designs
================
![abc-logo](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8985471/5062111/616ae9e6-6dab-11e4-96b9-4dbfa4a19d1c.gif)

>“Should a logo be self-explanatory?”

![ibm-logo](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8985471/5062112/624bc2f4-6dab-11e4-92aa-1df4a809b536.gif)

>“A logo does not sell (directly), it identifies.”

![ups-logo](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8985471/5062114/639938da-6dab-11e4-83df-559db89b41ab.gif)

>“I do not use humour consciously, I just go that way naturally”

