Massimo Vignelli
-----------------

Massimo Vignelli was an Italian designer who worked in a number of areas ranging from package design through houseware design and furniture design to public signage and showroom design. He was the co-founder of Vignelli Associates, with his wife, Lella.


![massimo_vignelli_photo](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8985471/5062204/94bb4e64-6dae-11e4-9d43-2a27b17c5617.jpg)

His work
========
His work includes graphic and corporate identity programs, publication designs, packaging, architectural graphics, exhibition, interior, furniture, and consumer product designs for leading American and European companies and institutions

![massimo-vignelli-1g](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8985471/5062173/9d1a46ba-6dad-11e4-8579-69469f042e96.jpg)
 bicentennial poster USA by vignelli associates, 1976

![designboom_massimo-vignelli_interview_003](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8985471/5062179/df538726-6dad-11e4-9b93-b854adfb92ab.jpg)

transportation graphics for new york subway

![designboom_massimo-vignelli_interview_006](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8985471/5062191/399b0f88-6dae-11e4-887d-ffc6b1c8c8b3.jpg)

heller packaging program by vignelli associates, 1968

![designboom_massimo-vignelli_interview_004](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8985471/5062192/3d03e870-6dae-11e4-9372-816080fd0ea2.jpg)

